                <h2>Pre-Check: Confirm Prerequisites for Budget Allocation</h2>
<p>Before allocating budget, operators need to confirm the following:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Monthly ad budget total</strong>: Clarify the monthly amount available for paid advertising.</li>
<li><strong>Core business metric targets</strong>: ROAS goals, customer acquisition cost limits, and order volume targets for this cycle.</li>
<li><strong>Main promoted products or categories</strong>: Core SKUs or categories for this period, to avoid budget scattering across too many product lines.</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Note</strong>: If ROAS targets haven't been set, refer to industry averages—utility apps typically target 1.5-2.0 ROAS, while e-commerce sites target 2.0-4.0, depending on average order value and margin space.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>Step 1: Determine Budget Ratios by Growth Phase</h2>
<p>Independent sites at different development stages require significantly different budget allocation strategies. Here are recommended frameworks for three typical phases:</p>
<h3>Phase A: Cold Start (Months 1-3)</h3>
<p><strong>Objective</strong>: Test creatives, validate audiences, accumulate conversion data.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Platform</th>
<th>Budget %</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Meta (Facebook/Instagram)</td>
<td>40-50%</td>
<td>Primary testing platform, flexible audience targeting</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Google Ads</td>
<td>30-40%</td>
<td>Test search intent and shopping ads</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TikTok</td>
<td>10-20%</td>
<td>Short video creative testing, lower cost</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Key Action</strong>: Keep individual creative budgets at 10-15% of total to avoid overspending on single creatives.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Phase B: Growth Stage (Months 3-6)</h3>
<p><strong>Objective</strong>: Scale effective creatives, optimize ROAS, increase order volume.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Platform</th>
<th>Budget %</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Google Ads</td>
<td>40-50%</td>
<td>Search and shopping ads as main traffic sources</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Meta (Facebook/Instagram)</td>
<td>30-40%</td>
<td>Retargeting and lookalike expansion</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TikTok</td>
<td>15-25%</td>
<td>Expand UGC-style creative deployment</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Key Action</strong>: Pause ad groups with ROAS below 1.5, reallocate budget to high-performing campaigns.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Phase C: Promotional Period (e.g., Black Friday)</h3>
<p><strong>Objective</strong>: Concentrate traffic, boost conversion rates.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Platform</th>
<th>Budget %</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Google Ads</td>
<td>45-55%</td>
<td>Shopping ads and Dynamic Search Ads</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Meta (Facebook/Instagram)</td>
<td>35-45%</td>
<td>Promotional creatives, intensive A/B testing</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TikTok</td>
<td>10-15%</td>
<td>Awareness-focused during pre-promotion phase</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Key Action</strong>: Start incremental spending 2 weeks before the promotion, avoid testing creatives on the day itself.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Step 2: Allocate Budget by Platform Type</h2>
<p>After determining ratios, further breakdown by campaign type:</p>
<h3>Google Ads Budget Breakdown</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Shopping Ads</strong>: 50-60% of Google total, promote high-converting SKUs.</li>
<li><strong>Search Ads</strong>: 20-30%, target core keywords like brand + category terms.</li>
<li><strong>Display Ads</strong>: 10-15%, for retargeting and reaching potential customers.</li>
<li><strong>YouTube Ads</strong>: 5-10%, suitable for teams with video assets.</li>
</ol>
<h3>Meta Budget Breakdown</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Dynamic Product Ads (DPA)</strong>: 40-50% of Meta total, high automation.</li>
<li><strong>Retargeting Ads</strong>: 25-30%, target abandoned cart and browse abandonment users.</li>
<li><strong>New Customer Acquisition Ads</strong>: 20-30%, using lookalike or interest targeting.</li>
<li><strong>Conversion vs. Brand Ads</strong>: Focus on conversion optimization initially, allocate 15% to brand awareness during promotions.</li>
</ol>
<h3>TikTok Budget Breakdown</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>In-Feed Ads</strong>: 60-70% of TikTok total, core focus on UGC-style content.</li>
<li><strong>Shopping Ads</strong>: 20-30%, prioritize testing in US and UK markets.</li>
<li><strong>TopView</strong>: Around 10%, temporarily increase during promotions.</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2>Step 3: Set Budget Adjustment Cadence</h2>
<p>Budget allocation isn't a one-time task—it requires periodic checks and adjustments:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Check Frequency</th>
<th>What to Review</th>
<th>Adjustment Actions</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Daily</td>
<td>Spending pace, CPC fluctuations</td>
<td>Pause campaigns with abnormal high spend</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Weekly</td>
<td>Campaign ROAS, conversion costs</td>
<td>Reallocate budget to high-performing campaigns</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Bi-weekly</td>
<td>Creative performance ranking</td>
<td>Pause creatives with CTR below 1% or CPA exceeding target by 30%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Monthly</td>
<td>Overall ROI, category performance</td>
<td>Adjust category budget ratios</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2>Step 4: Common Mistake Checklist</h2>
<p>Operators often make these mistakes when executing budget allocation:</p>
<ul>
<li>❌ Over-scattering budget: Testing 20+ campaigns simultaneously, none receiving sufficient budget.</li>
<li>❌ Neglecting retargeting: Spending all budget on new customer acquisition, missing value from existing customers.</li>
<li>❌ Demanding ROAS during cold start: Early phase should focus on data accumulation; demanding high ROAS too early misses potentially strong creatives.</li>
<li>❌ Adding budget for promotions without adjusting creatives: Promotional traffic costs 3-5x more, requiring targeted creatives.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>The core logic of e-commerce site ad budget allocation is: <strong>Phase determines ratio, platform determines structure, cadence determines adjustment</strong>.</p>
<p>Following this SOP framework, operators can start from confirming total budget, then gradually complete platform allocation, campaign breakdown, and periodic checks. It's recommended to first establish the basic structure within 1-2 weeks, then continuously optimize based on actual data.</p>
